# 📅 Day 5 – Storage & Error Handling (Save Resume Drafts)

## 🎓 Theory

### 🗂️ localStorage
- **Definition**: A built-in browser storage mechanism that stores key–value pairs persistently (data doesn’t disappear on reload/close).
- **Key Methods**:
  ```js
  localStorage.setItem("key", "value");   // Save
  localStorage.getItem("key");           // Retrieve
  localStorage.removeItem("key");        // Delete
  localStorage.clear();                  // Clear all
👉 Industry Use: Saving user login state (e.g., keeping a user logged in even after refresh).

# 💡 Creative Use: Auto-save today’s study plan or notes so they aren’t lost on refresh.

# ⚠️ try/catch
Definition: Error handling block in JavaScript to catch runtime errors without breaking the app.

Syntax:

js
Copy
Edit
try {
  // risky code
} catch (error) {
  console.error("Something went wrong:", error);
}
👉 Industry Use: Handling failed payment gateway request (e.g., Stripe/PayPal).

💡 Creative Use: Show a “Fallback Study Task” if AI study planner API fails.

📝 Assignments
Store & Retrieve Name

Save a user’s name in localStorage.

Retrieve and display it after page reload.

html
Copy
Edit
<input id="username" placeholder="Enter your name">
<button onclick="saveName()">Save</button>
<p id="displayName"></p>

<script>
  function saveName() {
    let name = document.getElementById("username").value;
    localStorage.setItem("userName", name);
    showName();
  }

  function showName() {
    let name = localStorage.getItem("userName");
    if (name) document.getElementById("displayName").innerText = "Welcome, " + name;
  }

  // Run on page load
  showName();
</script>
Fetch with try/catch

js
Copy
Edit
async function getData() {
  try {
    let res = await fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1");
    if (!res.ok) throw new Error("API request failed");
    let data = await res.json();
    console.log("Data:", data);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error caught:", error.message);
  }
}
getData();
🏗️ Project Task
Resume Builder Updates
Save Draft with localStorage

Save form fields (name, education, skills, etc.) into localStorage.

Retrieve them when the page reloads so progress isn’t lost.

js
Copy
Edit
function saveDraft() {
  let draft = {
    name: document.getElementById("name").value,
    education: document.getElementById("education").value,
    skills: document.getElementById("skills").value
  };
  localStorage.setItem("resumeDraft", JSON.stringify(draft));
}

function loadDraft() {
  let draft = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("resumeDraft"));
  if (draft) {
    document.getElementById("name").value = draft.name || "";
    document.getElementById("education").value = draft.education || "";
    document.getElementById("skills").value = draft.skills || "";
  }
}

// Run on page load
loadDraft();
Custom Error Messages for API Failures

Example: If job trends or AI cover letter API fails.

js
Copy
Edit
async function fetchJobTrends() {
  try {
    let res = await fetch("https://fake-api-for-trends.com");
    if (!res.ok) throw new Error("API unavailable");
    let data = await res.json();
    console.log("Job Trends:", data);
  } catch (error) {
    document.getElementById("jobTrends").innerText =
      "⚠️ Sorry! Unable to fetch job trends. Please try again later.";
  }
}
